FBIS4-55058 "dreeu090_m_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-090 Daily Report 9 May 1994 THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA Police Report on Illegal Border Crossings Police Report on Illegal Border Crossings AU0905144794 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 9 May 94 AU0905144794 Skopje MILS-NEWS English BFN [Unattributed report: "1,307 Cases of Illegal Crossings of Border"] [Text] The Police Department of Debar stated at a press conference that it has registered 1,307 cases of illegal crossings of the Macedonian-Albanian border (1,303 of them being Albanian citizens), in the period of January-April this year. 1,247 of the cases were underage youngsters, who have been returned to Albania by police intervention, whereas criminal charges have been brought against 56 individuals. The police representatives also informed of 11 border incidents near Debar in the same period.
